      <h2>Types of Shower We Install Across Liverpool</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We install every type of shower found in Liverpool homes. Here is how to choose the right one for your property and water supply.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Electric showers. Works on any water supply.</strong><p>An electric shower heats cold water on demand using an internal heating element. Entirely independent of the hot water system. It works even when the boiler is broken. The most popular choice for Liverpool properties with low water pressure or gravity-fed systems. Available in 7.5kW, 9.5kW and 10.8kW ratings. We recommend 9.5kW or above for comfortable shower performance.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Thermostatic mixer showers. The safest option for families.</strong><p>A thermostatic bar valve mixes hot and cold water to a pre-set temperature and maintains it even when someone runs a tap elsewhere in the house. The anti-scald protection makes thermostatic showers the recommended choice for families with children or elderly residents. We supply and fit from £300 including the bar valve, head and riser rail.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Power showers. Boost low pressure systems.</strong><p>A power shower has an integral pump to boost water pressure in homes with gravity-fed systems where the pressure is too low for a satisfying shower. Requires a hot water cylinder. Cannot be used with a combi boiler. Very effective in Liverpool's older Victorian and Edwardian properties with gravity-fed systems. Supply and fit from £350.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Digital showers. Precise control and smart features.</strong><p>A digital shower controller allows precise temperature setting from a remote pad or smartphone app. Available in wireless and wired configurations. Popular in larger Liverpool properties and new en suite installations where a premium shower experience is wanted. Supply and fit from £500 for the valve and controller.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Walk-in showers and wet areas. No tray required.</strong><p>A walk-in shower area uses a linear drain and a level-access tiled floor rather than a shower tray. Requires full tanking of the walls and floor before tiling. We carry out the full installation including waterproofing, tiling and the shower valve. Walk-in areas without a tray from £800 supply and fit including tiling.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Shower over bath. Practical for smaller Liverpool homes.</strong><p>A shower over bath with a folding bath screen is one of the most space-efficient solutions for smaller Liverpool homes or rental properties. We install electric shower over bath from £200 and thermostatic bar valve over bath from £250. Bath screens from £150 supply and fit.</p></div></div>
      </div>
